The solution in `acronym.js`:
- Replaces hyphens with spaces (they're word separators)
- Removes underscores and apostrophes (punctuation to strip)
- Splits on whitespace, takes the first letter of each word, uppercases it, and joins them

```js
export const parse = (phrase) => {
  const cleaned = phrase.replace(/-/g, ' ').replace(/[_']/g, '');
  return cleaned.split(/\s+/).filter(Boolean).map(word => word[0].toUpperCase()).join('');
};
```

